# üêû bug report

### Affected Package
<!-- Can you pin-point one or more @angular/* packages as the source of the bug? -->
The issue is caused by package @angular/localize


### Is this a regression?

<!-- Did this behavior use to work in the previous version? -->
No.


### Description
Angular generates functions called "_templateObjectXYZ" (XYZ is number) for purpose of runtime translations. These functions are defined in the global scope. This is not a problem when the code is loaded using ES6 modules. But for differential loading (ES5) with multiple chunks, these names collide between JS files. And overwrites each other (ES6 modules are isolated from each other and thus there is no problem)

An example:

chunk1.js:
```
function _templateObject27() {
  var data = _taggedTemplateLiteral([":@@reservationDisabledMsg\u241Fae7be3f0e6729c98b02e1124df8a77aad6ee9f30\u241F1393106427250937902:VAlpha"]);

  _templateObject27 = function _templateObject27() {
    return data;
  };

  return data;
}
```


chunk2.js:
```
function _templateObject27() {
  var data = _taggedTemplateLiteral([":@@pricesWithVatMsg\u241Fe346e0c62e86724c7d4234ff4bbd0135ff1fe127\u241F527442591666970432:VBeta."]);

  _templateObject27 = function _templateObject27() {
    return data;
  };

  return data;
}
```

This leads to incorrect translations. The result depends on the order in which they are loaded (because one function overrides other).

The solution would be to not placing these functions into the global scope. Or do not reset the counter for "_templateObjectXYZ" function name genration between chunks. 



## üåç  Your Environment

Angular Version: 9.1

Hello,

I am currently doing deep research on Angular and ways to improve the performances in Angular, So I  have created the simple Angular application having two routes and whenever users try to load any routes, I wanted to show them App shell before actually page is displayed.

Expected Behaviour: When users try to access http://localhost:8080/home or http://localhost:8080/tutorials the App Shell component should display until the resources downloaded and then the actual content of the '/home' or '/tutorials' should be displayed

Actual Behaviour: When I am trying to access http://localhost:8080/home or http://localhost:8080/tutorials only the App shell content is displayed but it's not showing the actual content of the route, so the issue is app shell component is persistent and actual content of the route is not displayed

**Steps to Reproduce**

- Created the new angular application with `ng new`

- Added the angular app shell using `ng generate app-shell`

- Build the application with `ng run angular-with-app-shell:app-shell`

- Run the application with Node and Express with `node server.js` and server.js having 

```
var express = require('express');
var app = express();
var path = require('path');

app.get('/*', function(req, res) {
    res.sendFile(path.join(__dirname + '/dist/angular-with-app-shell/browser/index.html'));
});

app.listen(8080);
```

And I have created reproduction Git Repository here 
[https://github.com/mvgadagi/angular-with-app-shell](https://github.com/mvgadagi/angular-with-app-shell)

Please let me know if any other details required

Thanks & Regards,
Mahesh

